\title{Random Walk Fusion}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Navigate skill graphs via deterministic random walks. Fuses derivational chains, algebraic structure, color determinism, and bidirectional flow for skill recombination.}

\subtree{
\title{Random Walk Fusion: Skill Graph Navigation}
\p{\strong{Status}: ✅ Production Ready \strong{Trit}: +1 (PLUS - generative recombination) \strong{Principle}: skill_{n+1} = walk(seed_n, graph_n) \strong{Frame}: Skills as nodes, concepts as edges, walks as derivations}

\subtree{
\title{Overview}
\p{\strong{Random Walk Fusion} traverses skill graphs using deterministic random walks to discover novel skill combinations. Each step derives from the previous via seed chaining, producing reproducible concept-blending paths.}

\pre{\startverb
seed₀ → skill₀ → concept₀ → seed₁ → skill₁ → concept₁ → ...
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Fused Components}
\pre{\startverb
| Source Skill | Contribution | Integration |
|--------------|--------------|-------------|
| **unworld** | Derivational chains | Walk succession is derivational, not temporal |
| **acsets** | Algebraic structure | Skills form C-set: functor from schema to Set |
| **gay-mcp** | Color determinism | Each step gets deterministic (color, trit) |
| **world-hopping** | Bidirectional flow | Walks are reversible via involution |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Core Formula}
\pre{\startverb
# Walk step: derive next position from current state + skill trit
next_seed = (current_seed ⊕ (skill_trit × γ)) × MIX  mod 2⁶⁴
next_skill = skills[next_seed mod |skills|]

where:
  γ   = 0x9E3779B9  (golden ratio, 32-bit)
  MIX = 0x85EBCA6B  (mixing constant)
  ⊕   = XOR
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Skill Graph Schema (ACSet)}
\pre{\startverb
@present SchSkillGraph(FreeSchema) begin
  Skill::Ob          # Skill nodes
  Concept::Ob        # Concept edges
  Walk::Ob           # Walk trajectories
  
  src::Hom(Concept, Skill)
  tgt::Hom(Concept, Skill)
  step::Hom(Walk, Skill)
  
  Trit::AttrType
  Color::AttrType
  trit::Attr(Skill, Trit)
  color::Attr(Walk, Color)
end
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Walk Operations}
\subtree{
\title{1. Forward Walk (Derivational)}
\pre{\startverb
walk = RandomWalkFusion.new(seed: 0x42D, graph: skill_graph)
path = walk.forward(steps: 7)
# => [{skill: "unworld", concept: "derivational", color: "#D8267F", trit: +1}, ...]
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Backward Walk (Involution)}
\pre{\startverb
reversed = walk.backward(path)
# ι∘ι = id verified: returns to origin seed
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Branching Walk (Triadic)}
\pre{\startverb
branches = walk.triadic_split
# => { minus: path_minus, ergodic: path_ergodic, plus: path_plus }
# GF(3) conserved at each step across branches
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Hop Walk (World-Hopping)}
\pre{\startverb
target = skill_graph.find("epistemic-arbitrage")
path = walk.hop_to(target, via: :triangle_inequality)
# Uses accessibility relation and distance metric
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{GF(3) Conservation}
\p{Each walk maintains GF(3) balance:}

\pre{\startverb
sum(trits) ≡ 0 (mod 3)
\stopverb}

\p{When imbalanced, the walk applies \strong{rebalancing moves}:}

\ul{
\li{Insert neutral (trit=0) skill}
\li{Pair complementary trits (+1, -1)}
\li{Branch to triadic stream}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Fusion Algebra}
\p{The fusion of concepts follows ACSet composition:}

\pre{\startverb
unworld ∘ gay-mcp = derivational color chains
acsets ∘ world-hopping = accessible skill functors
(unworld ∘ acsets) ∘ (gay-mcp ∘ world-hopping) = random-walk-fusion
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Commands}
\pre{\startverb
# Run random walk
bb skill_random_walk.bb [seed]

# Skill-specific walks
just walk-skills seed=0x42D steps=12
just walk-triadic seed=0x42D
just walk-hop from=unworld to=acsets

# Verify walk properties
just walk-verify seed=0x42D  # Check GF(3), involution
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{API}
\pre{\startverb
require 'random_walk_fusion'

# Initialize walker
fusion = RandomWalkFusion.new(
  seed: 0x42D,
  skills: SkillGraph.load("~/.agents/skills")
)

# Execute walk
path = fusion.walk(steps: 7)

# Get fusion concepts
fusion.concepts
# => ["derivational chains", "algebraic structure", "color determinism", "bidirectional flow"]

# Recombine to new skill
new_skill = fusion.recombine(path)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Example Output}
\pre{\startverb
╔═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║  SKILL RANDOM WALK - Derivational Traversal                   ║
╚═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

  Step 0: epistemic-arbitrage  │ knowledge gaps │ [#98FF4C] ○
  Step 1: world-hopping        │ bidirectional flow │ [#9C4CFF] ○
  Step 2: bisimulation-game    │ game equivalence │ [#8E4CFF] −
  Step 3: epistemic-arbitrage  │ knowledge gaps │ [#4CA2FF] +
  Step 4: world-hopping        │ bidirectional flow │ [#4CFF88] −
  Step 5: triad-interleave     │ tripartite streams │ [#FF974C] ○
  Step 6: world-hopping        │ bidirectional flow │ [#FF4CB2] −

  GF(3) Sum: 1 (balanced: ✗)

  Fusion Concepts:
    → Derivational chains (unworld) guide walk succession
    → Algebraic structure (acsets) defines skill graph schema
    → Color determinism (gay-mcp) assigns trit/color per step
    → Bidirectional flow (world-hopping) enables path reversal
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Philosophical Foundation}
\p{Random walks on skill graphs embody \strong{xenomodern recombination}:}

\ol{
\li{\strong{No privileged origin}: Any skill can seed the walk}
\li{\strong{Deterministic exploration}: Same seed → same discoveries}
\li{\strong{Compositional}: Walks compose via path concatenation}
\li{\strong{Reversible}: Every walk has its involution dual}
}

\p{The fusion is not additive but \strong{multiplicative} — concepts don't just accumulate, they transform each other through the walk.}

\p{\strong{Skill Name}: random-walk-fusion \strong{Type}: Skill Graph Navigation / Concept Recombination \strong{Trit}: +1 (PLUS) \strong{GF(3)}: Conserved via rebalancing \strong{Walk}: Derivational, deterministic, bidirectional}
}
}